The car maker says more than 7,000 of the vehicles are being recalled over airbag issues. JOHANNESBURG - Mitsubishi South Africa has issued a preventative recall of thousands of Pajeros.In a short statement released this afternoon, the car maker says more than 7,000 of the vehicles are being recalled in this country over airbag issues.Its part of a global recall after the Takata Corporation last year declared its air bags defectiveAt least 11 deaths were reported in the United States linked to airbags that ruptured.We'll have more on this breaking story in Eyewitness News throughout the day.